            { para: 2, text: '冻坏了吧？快洗手，饭好了！', technique: '语言描写（母亲声音）', techniqueEn: 'Maternal Voice as Warmth', effect: '三句话=关心+指令+好消息——妈妈的语言结构就是爱的结构', effectEn: 'Concern, instruction, good news — three clauses that map the architecture of maternal love' },
            { para: 3, text: '从舌尖一直暖到胃里', technique: '五感描写（通感）', techniqueEn: 'Taste-to-Warmth Synesthesia', effect: '味觉→触觉的跨感官描写——把"吃饭"变成了"被爱包裹"', effectEn: 'Taste slides into temperature — eating becomes being enveloped, and the warmth is not from the food but from the person who cooked it' },
            { para: 3, text: '妈妈坐在对面，看着我吃，自己只夹了几筷子青菜', technique: '细节描写（无声母爱）', techniqueEn: 'Silent Maternal Sacrifice', effect: '自己不吃肉只看孩子吃——一个动作胜过一万字的"妈妈爱我"', effectEn: 'Watching her child eat meat while picking at greens — one gesture that renders ten thousand words of "my mother loves me" unnecessary' },
            { para: 4, text: '当时我觉得这不过是一顿普通的晚饭', technique: '欲扬先抑', techniqueEn: 'Deliberate Understatement', effect: '轻描淡写的一句话设置了后面"醒悟"的空间', effectEn: 'Calling it "just an ordinary dinner" creates the exact gap the rest of the essay will fill with meaning' },
            { para: 5, text: '不难吃，但总觉得少了什么', technique: '对比（缺失感）', techniqueEn: 'Absence as Revelation', effect: '盒饭vs妈妈的饭——不说"想家"，只说"少了什么"，更含蓄更有力', effectEn: 'Boxed meals that taste fine but feel wrong — the narrator cannot name what is missing, and that namelessness is the essay\'s engine' },
            { para: 7, text: '少了那个推开门的瞬间，少了那句"饭好了"，少了妈妈看我吃饭时那种满足的表情', technique: '排比（顿悟）', techniqueEn: 'Triple-Absence Epiphany', effect: '三个"少了"层层递进——从感官到语言到表情，越来越深', effectEn: 'Three "missing" clauses deepen from sensation to sound to expression — each layer peels closer to the core' },
            { para: 8, text: '红烧肉的香味又来了。这一次，我没有觉得"普通"', technique: '首尾呼应（认知转变）', techniqueEn: 'Circular Return with Transformed Eyes', effect: '同一碗红烧肉，不同的感受——结构上的呼应就是成长的证明', effectEn: 'The same braised pork, a different child — structural repetition becomes proof that understanding has changed' },
            { para: 11, text: '你只需要有一天忽然"缺少"了它，就会发现它一直都在', technique: '议论升华（以小见大）', techniqueEn: 'Philosophical Close', effect: '从一顿饭升华到人生哲理——幸福的本质是"失去后才懂"', effectEn: 'A dinner becomes a life principle: happiness is not found by seeking but by losing it once and recognizing it was always there' }
